(5/5)
I wanted to see what were some reasons for not wanting to learn about NFT and see if I could help address them to get more people into the space. 

Thank you to everyone who responded on the last post.

(4/5)
In the end a user would learn:
- How to set up a wallet
- How to buy crypto from an exchange and transfer to a wallet
- Mint a NFT from a site
- Post a NFT for sale
- Purchase a NFT from a marketplace

(3/5)
I created a Rinkeby Testnet contract and mint site for people to learn and experience the process and allowing them to use their wallet but not have to risk using real money

(2/5)
Users complete each step and are sent an â€œachievementâ€ NFT which is a NFT created on Polygon for free.

Once they receive the NFT they use CollabLand to verify and gain a role to access the next level
